description:
Zanotto continues to explore the post-apocalyptic world in which our heroine, a beautiful warrior originally from a tribe of Amazons that she had to flee, continues her quest.

She reach a mining colony where all the inhabitants were massacred, except for a little girl with tongue cut out, which can only communicate by thought.
name: Le Cristal Rouge

description:
Brad, Shere Khan and Falka form a strange trio. Their paths cross and they do not have the choice to team.

Brad is already in possession of blue crystal, one of the three elements which, when assembled, form a single crystal. Shere Khaan, for his part, knows the way of the Fountains of Fire, as well as where to find the missing red crystal.

Falka? She only wants to deliver Sol, prisoner of a tribe of mutants. But she is aware of the help that can be provided by two men. Needed help because bounty hunters are determined to kill Sol, and are perilously close.
name: Le Grand Secret

description: Hard boiled detectives, high speed car chases, brain harvesting aliens and adulterous martians! If you like your comics fun and freaky, you've come to the right place.

As Magnanimo's new sidekick, Roger is now a virtual prisoner in the superhero's "Fortress of Fraternity". But before he can even settle in for his first night he gets word that the big plan to protect his family from super-villains by removing him from home may have already backfired! He's gotta get back there! But wait! He's rooming with a superhero! Mo will help! Or will he? OR CAN he... Especially when they find a new totally destructive and really annoying menace zeroing in on BOTH of them at that very moment....!

After escaping the destruction of the Pipeline facility and surviving the explosion, Captain Reed, Sergeant Dixon and the freed scientist, Dr. Creighton are lost in the darkness of a system of underground railway tunnels. Meanwhile, above ground the Mustangs deal with the possible loss of two of their teammates. But the squad must place the mission first and provide security for the Army CBRN units looking for clues about Adzic's secret plan in the aftermath. The fight is not over yet in America's Army #10 - Point of Contact.
name: Point of Contact

description:
Under the Dream Queen's thrall, Mary finally manages to break free and recover her short term memory. Outraged she's hauled away to toil in the palace kitchen making pies, where she finds her spellbound companions performing menial chores. Queen Amorpha seeks to separate her from any hope of restoring Mother Night forever. Meanwhile, Shroom and Oaken discover a key secret bringing Mary the means to fight the Queen's magic.

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Superpowers Don't Pay the Rent

As Lightning finds himself suddenly in debt and unable to pay his creditors, he turns to "unconventional" means of generating revenue. While Lt. Lightning's relationship with his girlfriend further implodes over his woes, the Manticore's love life takes a turn for the better.
name: Superpowers Don't Pay the Rent

description: The serialized fun continues from pages of Joe Daly's full graphic novel Dungeon Quest: Book Two, the adventure continues in issue #5. It turns out the river troll was guarding the entrance to an ancient sewer system. What other treasures are in there? Time to LEVEL UP.

The serialized fun continues from pages of Joe Daly's full graphic novel Dungeon Quest: Book Two, the adventure continues in the last installment, issue #6. The ancient sewer system leaves to a pools of leaves where the gang are lead around by a glo-baby. But where, oh where, is Bromedes? Is the gang one step closer or further away from assembling the Atlantean guitar?

Downfall Part 3

Downfall continues as the Heroes of Echo Company are captured and Freedom station plummets toward the Earth.
name: Downfall Part 3

description:
The Walking Drunk

When the beer runs dry at Holidaze, the staff tries to substitute with an old non-alcoholic brew that's been in the stockroom for years. Will their iconic patrons notice the difference? Or is it just possible their alcohol-infused systems will reject anything but true booze and turn them into monstrous, beer-craving husks of flesh?! Nah, that would never happen...
name: The Walking Drunk

description:
Tommy's Peninsula - part 2

Tommy leads Marlowe and Larry through the spooky caves of the peninsula where they find more clues to what happened to the missing animals.
name: Tommy's Peninsula Part 2

description:
"That's Really SUPER, Kevin!" Kevin's world takes a surprising new twist when he becomes the masked crime fighter called "The Equalizer!" Of course, this doesn't just happen overnight. When he saves someone's life and becomes a media sensation, Veronica's wheels start turning and with her drive, determination (and unlimited cash!) she molds a new career for Kevin! Somewhat apprehensive, will Kevin move forward as a superhero? And what will happen to his everyday teenage life? Find out in the first part of this exciting new storyline!

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverDan Parent1
VarVariant CoverPhil Jimenez2

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: That's Really SUPER, Kevin!

description: WWII brought the world to its knees, as nations scrambled to fight and defend against strengthening foes and common enemies. But beyond the battlefield, a secret war was being fought. A race to develop weapons of fear that would provide ultimate power to those who possessed them. Born from this pursuit would be two of the most serious and deadly creations ever known to man. The United States would develop the Atomic bomb, the pinnacle of nuclear science. While in Japan, a rogue military Doctor designed a killer plague, hell-bent on destroying his enemies.
name: Horrors of War

description:
Kill the Body and the Head Will Die

While investigating the disappearance of Duke David Oberg, McBlack follows the clues to a dog park and a monster truck sales yard... but after tangling with a gang of redneck triads and a mixed municipal soccer team, the bodies are piling up faster than the clues. The case is not at all what it seems, but suddenly McBlack has bigger problems: an old enemy has rolled back into town and it's all Old Smiley can do to keep his head on his shoulders.
name: Kill the Body and the Head Will Die

description: Sure, it sucks to be a zombie, but what happens when it sucks to take care of one? The Samsa's family's struggles reach their gory conclusion!

Recovering from the edge of death, rescued by the mysterious young man who set this plot into motion in the first place, Naja returns to Japan only to make a horrific discovery. The stakes are raised, and unlikely allies find themselves fighting side by side against an even more mysterious foe...
Who Pulled The Trigger? This Special Edition includes never before seen inked and pencilled art!
name: Open Your Eye

description:
Paul Tobin (Bandette, Prometheus) and Ron Chan (The Guild, Husbands) deliver the second chapter in their hysterical, all-ages Plants vs. Zombies: Timepocalypse series! Racing to beat Zomboss before the zombie leader can recover the parts he needs to rebuild his ominous Sun Vacuum, young adventurers Patrice Blazing and Nate Timely travel through different eras to find those machine parts first—and to fend off a “fun-dead” invasion that threatens all timelines! Using Crazy Dave’s mysterious, time-warping recreational vehicle, the two heroes head to ancient Egypt to snag one of Zomboss’s missing doodads! One will remain to fight zombies in the past. The other will face a threat possibly more hideous: A 1970s disco dance contest!

The hit video game returns to comics!

A humor-filled adventure that all ages can enjoy!

Tobin and Chan take us on another original Plants vs. Zombies adventure!

A new Plants vs. Zombies comic-book series!

In this issue, Crazy Dave, Patrice, and Nate visit ancient Egypt in an attempt to find all the missing sun vacuum parts before Zomboss's zombies do.

Nate and Dave end up taking a side trip to a 1970s dance-off to find another part while Patrice stays in Egypt. Nate almost loses everything to a Disco Zombie, but Crazy Dave puts on a tour-de-force dance and wins the part. Returning to ancient Egypt, they find that Patrice has been crowned Queen of Egypt, and has her part as well.

They fly off to another time in search of more pieces.

Don't Rain on my Parade

The team are out, but how does the world feel about that? The Bear's secrets are revealed! Basher goes on a daring and dangerous mission somehow connected to The Pride.

As if that wasn't trouble enough, the World's Premier Super Team, the Justice Division, come knocking. It never does go that smoothly when superhero teams meet up, does it?
name: Don't Rain On My Parade

description: The first chapter of "Seven Deadly Finns," introducing the Prong Murderer — New York City's most infamous serial killer! Driven by a sinister voice from inside his mind, this fearsome opponent is cutting a bloody swath through the Big Apple… directly on a collision course towards The Shadow. Meanwhile, the Finn crime family grips the city in a stranglehold, and The Shadow's agents begin to show dissension in the ranks!
name: Seven Deadly Finns

description:
Sonic Super Digest returns with an ALL-NEW STORY continuing the hit SONIC ORIGINS mini-feature! Sonic the Hedgehog has many friends, but few are as brave, stalwart or had as much growth as Antoine D’Coolette! Learn how this skittish swordsman crossed paths with Sonic and the Freedom Fighters as only Sonic Super Digest can tell it! Then, continue the fun with more classic adventures from the Sonic comic library! The new Sonic universe is full of wonder and excitement as only Archie Comics can bring!

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Little Lost Soldier

description: With Santilli on a gunship and out of the city, E.D.G.E. defence forces fight back against the alien infestation within City-012, determined to end it by any means necessary. But Santilli holds the secret that could save the city, and perhaps everyone inside it. Will Forrester and Goldstein fulfil their mission and get Santilli to safety, or will they return and bring an end to the carnage? The exciting third issue of Telikos Protocol brings the first arc to an explosive close, with creators Peter Cooper (writer) and Adam Burn (artist) providing an action-packed outing that will leave you breathless!

PUBLIC ENEMY NUMBER ONE! WINDBLADE seeks out the last refuge she has left, the living city METROPLEX as his malfunctions intensify! WINDBLADE realizes that even if she survives STARSCREAM, METROPLEX himself may doom them all!

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

RegRegular CoverSarah Stone1
SubSubscription CoverPhil Jimenez (a) & Romulo Fajardo Jr. (c)2
RI30th Anniversary Retailer Incentive CoverPhil Jimenez (a) & Romulo Fajardo Jr. (c)3

When OLIN KLIEN decides to use an experimental fighter plane to save a U.E.D.C. base under attack by the Mechani, it’s up to Trimaxx to save the day. Yet Mo may be up the creek as she faces a powerful threat that may put an end to her and Olin permanently!
Tyler Lockwood left Mystic Falls after his mother’s murder, and is hiding with a werewolf pack in the Appalachians. But Katherine Pierce’s arrival ends his peaceful plans for the summer!
name: Loyal Dogs Part 1 of 3

description:
A group of vampires who claim to be nonviolent and non-predatory, try to settle in a small southern town. When problems escalate between 'Bloods' (vampires) and 'Beats' (non-infected humans), the military special operations unit, V-8, rolls in to contain the situation. This one doesn't end well for anyone.

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Red State

description:
Special Rurouni Kenshin: Master of Flame chapter! Part one of a special limited series that focuses on the story of Kenshin's archrival, Shishio Makoto! Plus, the final chapter of Stealth Symphony! Find out what happens in the thrilling conclusion! And in Naruto, Squad 7 stops playing defense, and hatches a plan to turn the table on Kaguya! All that and more!

Table of Contents

MangaChapter #Chapter Name
Rurouni Kenshin: Master Of FlamesPart 1000
World Trigger67Invasion: Part 16
Naruto684We Ought To Kill Him
Hunter X Hunter346Options
Toriko284Toriko's Resolution!!
Bleach588The Headless Star 7
Nisekoi130Interview
Stealth Symphony20About That Man's Invisibility, Part 5
name: No. 33, July 14, 2014

description:
The saga of Scully and Wynn continues as they search for a fabled village by the sea where rumors tell of a warm heaven in this cold hell. Wynn is still in search of her parents and the village of La Niña may be the place they were heading when she was abandoned as a child. Scully just wants to find enough fuel to keep their new vehicle on the move. But will they find death at the end of the icy road?

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverJackson Butch Guice1
SubSubscription CoverGerardo Zaffino2

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

The New York Times bestselling novel now adapted into comics, featuring full-color illustrations by Hugo Award-nominated artist Jimmy Broxton, and as adapted by fan-favorite writers Jimmy Palmiotti and Justin Gray. This contemporary dystopian classic--hailed by Justin Cronin, New York Times bestselling author of The Passage, as "an epic feat of imagination"--will captivate readers both familiar and new. This is the story of mankind clawing for survival, of mankind on the edge. The world outside has grown unkind, the view of it limited, talk of it forbidden. But there are always those who hope, who dream. These are the dangerous people, the residents who infect others with their optimism. Their punishment is simple. They are given the very thing they profess to want: They are allowed outside. In issue #4 of 6: The time has come: To take arms, take action, and take back humanity's future…

After nearly destroying a taping of Monday Night Raw, CM Punk, Daniel Bryan, and Rey Mysterio are desperate to discover who or what was responsible for them losing their memories and acting berserk. But each Superstar remembers the night differently and their contradictory recollections are pulling them apart just when they should be working together - particularly when Batista is gunning for all them after their hi-jinks cost him a title shot. And things take a turn to the bizarre when Goldust attempts his own unique style of help.
name: Haze of Glory!, Part Two: Shattered Dreams

description:
Agent Mulder has been infected with black oil, playing host to an alien being seeking to use his knowledge, history, and expertise to unlock something mysteriously and terribly powerful. But Mulder and the would-be alien colonist possessing him aren't the only ones looking for it...

List of covers and their creators:

RegRegular CoverFrancesco Francavilla1
RIRetailer Incentive CoverMark McHaley2
SubSubscription CoverPhoto3

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Pilgrims, Part 4

description:
Cover: James Biggie (Judge Dredd, Durham Red, Rogue Trooper, Tharg)

  • Judge Dredd - Jinxed! (Emma Beeby - Eoin Coveney)
  • Robo-Hunter - The Bødj Job (Alec Worley - Mark Simmons)
  • Future Shocks - The Exposé (Jody LeHeup - Jefte Palo)
  • Durham Red - The Calling (Robert Murphy - Duane Redhead)
  • Orlok - Agent of East-Meg One (Arthur Wyatt - Jake Lynch)
  • Rogue Trooper - Dregs of War (Guy Adams - Darren Douglas)
  • Star Scans: PSI-Judge Anderson (art: Fay Dalton) and Sláine (art: Ben Wilsher)
name: 2000AD Sci-Fi Special 2014

description: Every video game in town has been stolen! Three friends band together to get them back in an adventure where there are no extra lives!

“I came to wrench everything away from you. Your house, your wealth and, of course, your virginity.” Maggie’s father has died, leaving a debt behind. At his funeral, Maggie meets a man she has never wanted to see again. His name is Caleb Cameron, a global businessman who used numerous ruthless tactics to drive Maggie’s father to the brink and his company and family to ruins. Caleb approaches Maggie slowly with a cold, cruel smile as if toying with the family’s future. Maggie knows what Caleb wants—“He’s never forgotten that night six months ago.”
name: Vol. 1

description:
Bunny & Rink: The Friendship Begins

Bunny is a platypus ninja. Rink is a cafe manager, and a ninja. They met one day when Bunny was eating garbage in front of Rink's cafe. Friendship ensued.

Join Bunny and Rink on their first ever adventure full of Bat Ninjas! Moped Ninjas! Ninjamobiles! Shopping Ninjas! Regular Ninjas! Robots (Non-Ninja)! Wrestling! And Friendship!
name: The Friendship Begins

description: A unique tale of King Arthur and his Knights of the Round Table. Here, King Arthur did not die in the last epic battle against his bastard son Modred and his evil army but instead continued to rule the kingdom of Camelot. However, the divisions amongst his men continue and he struggles to maintain control of the kingdom. Modred also survived the battle, now a prisoner in Merlin's dungeon, and more of the bastard son is revealed as well as he plans revenge against his father. Collects issues 1-4.
name: Volume One

description: A Digital-First title! What Sarah Wesson doesn't know about her husband to be, Jon Smith, is that he is the world first super villain, pardoned for reasons unknown.
name: Happily Ever After...

description: A collection of short stories from the pages of Deadworld, one of the longest running zombie titles in the comics market. It is a world that has suffered a supernatural holocaust and the dead rise to walk again. Yet this world also has intelligent zombies, such as the Harley-riding, chain smoking King Zombie and they threaten to drive humankind into extinction. Included in this collection is the very first Deadworld story, "Black Sabbath". The classic tales illustrated by the artist known as "the Deadworld artist", Vince Locke, are presented as is the introduction to one of Deadworld's most popular characters, the Dead-Killer. In Deadworld, death is only the beginning of the horror and this action packed assemblage of tales set in this zombie infested world illustrates perfectly the dilemma the humans face, not only from the hordes of zombies but from other humans themselves.
name: TPB

description: A pansexual horror love story! In a post-apocalyptic future, three demons live and love as one among the ruined wastes. But eating rats and making love only goes so far when jealousy comes into play. What will happen when their polyamory falls apart? Find out in the pages of Death's Door!

Betty Cooper is embarking on her first year of high school. It’s sure to be filled with ups and downs, but with her trusty diary by her side, she’ll be able to get through it all. She’s a smart girl with a kind heart, so her freshman year should be easy-peasy, right? Well, throw in some major BFF drama with her longtime pal Veronica Lodge and things get off to a rocky start. Veronica’s rich, ruthless and snobby—the total opposite of Betty. And in high school where social status means EVERYTHING, Betty and Veronica can’t be the same besties they once were. Everyone’s favorite girl-next-door is diving head first into her high school career and extracurricular activities—from dog training to peer mediation to BMX competitions, Betty Cooper can do it all—but can she get by WITHOUT a little help from her friend? Find out in this heartwarming tale of the scariness that is starting high school in Archie's first-ever venture into the hugely popular journal series, with DIARY OF A GIRL NEXT DOOR: BETTY.
name: TPB

volume.name: Diary of A Girl Next Door: Betty

description: "What? We're not divorced?" Renee, who runs a catering business, receives unexpected news one day. The divorce papers that should have been processed seven years ago were never submitted. She is still married to her husband, Flynn! But this may be an unexpected opportunity. She doesn't need a husband, but wants a child. Since she is still his wife, she wonders if a sperm bank where her husband's sperm has been stored will let her use it. When Flynn learns of Renee's plan, he reacts to it positively and offers his help.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Girl troubles? Yes!

Fenada: In Good Spirits is a 24 page comedy about three friends, relationships and alcohol.

Flinch is a collection of engaging stories by established and emerging creators, all playing on their interpretation of 'flinch'.

From facing the 'other' within ourselves, to the tale of a prison inmate discovering what keeps him going, to a handful of stories exploring traditional (and non-traditional) hauntings alike.
name: Vol. 1

description: Celebrating 10 years of Jason being published in the US, this comic-book-format one-shot is a Jason fan's dream, with lots of previously unpublished Jason strips and artwork, an interview with Jason's colorist Hubert, a checklist of all Jason's books, a Q&A with the man himself, and a visual tributes gallery by several American cartoonists to the towering, taciturn Norwegian genius including Michael Allred, Kim Deitch, and Rich Tommaso.

Magic, Joy and Fantastic Coincidence

Join Preshea and her friend Tanya on a magical journey through a magical Victorian England!
name: Magic, Joy and Fantastic Coincidence

description: Based off the New York Times best selling novels. The Iron King is the first book in the Iron Fey series, and follows the adventures of a girl named Meghan Chase. On her sixteenth birthday, Meghan discovers her little brother has been kidnapped by a faery race known as "the Fey" and even worse, replaced with an evil changeling and taken into the "Nevernever." Meghan bravely ventures into the faery realm to rescue him, and that's where an epic plot unfolds. This collected edition has never before images and character designs!
name: TPB

description:
In the kingdom, mankind has never existed, animals have evolved in place of man's absence. However, as with humanity, there are good and evil beings in this realm.

Our story begins in the midst of a civil war between apekind that has ravaged the lands and threatens to engulf the rest of animal kind in its struggle for power and survival.
name: Rise of the Ape King Chapter One

description: At the turn of a new century, the world is caught between an opulent but oppressive empire and a growing underground resistance. Right in the middle is unlikely soldier and revolutionary Aeron Marloes. Her task: infiltrate the military, rise to the top, and assassinate the Emperor. But how far can she go to seize her promotion, the next step to her final goal? Does the end really justify the means? Marionette is a tale of slipping morality, of politics and treason, of revolution and revenge.

Sitting outside the dance floor at her cousin's wedding reception, Matty notices a man beside her and says hello. His name: Sebastian. A banker from New York. They start to hit it off, and Matty decides he is the ideal companion...for now. That's right—no matter how much Matty enjoys the relationship, she refuses to get too close to any man. That is the decision she made after her own carelessness cost her the use of her legs. Goodbye, Handsome. Little did Matty know that the man in question was determined to take the woman in the wheelchair out on a date!
name: Vol. 1

description: A massive battle between skyscraping giant robots leaves two pilots stranded in their vehicle after is incapacitated in combat. Trapped inside the giant metal corpse, their situation turns desperate…

If you stare at the moon too long, it will consume you. In this haunting collection of stories, emotions sparkle bright and warm, but they also sink into cold darkness as love and hate twist together to become one. When life slips out of control, and there's a whisper in your ear telling you to give in and blame it all on the moon, what will you do? Will you comfort or crush? Maybe, just maybe, you'll do both. On a moonlit night, not a single man in MOON CENTAUR will remain the same.

Contents

  • Face
  • Morning Moon
  • Moon Mirror
  • Let the Gentle Rain Fall
  • We'll Walk in July
  • Moon Centaur
name: Vol. 1

description:
There’s something for everyone in Koshino's first collection, My Neighbor: Inumaru was perfectly (un)happy working as a convenience store manager, so when Sakura literally drops in on him, he’s exposed to a whole new world – one he's certainly not used to. How will this change his perspective? For 10 years Kawabata held sweet memories of his first love, Nishijima...until they end up trapped in a factory together during a snowstorm with absolutely no one around. Left with only each other for warmth, will Kawabata be able to restrain himself? Plagued by his neighbor's incessant alarm clock every morning, Higashi decides to take matters into his own hands, only, he's given a key instead?! How did one innocent little key change the lives of two men? How far will you trust your neighbor? Find out about these and more in Koshino’s My Neighbor!

Story Titles

  • Falling For The Store Manager
  • Falling For The Store Manager 2
  • Borderline Passion
  • Before the Misunderstanding
  • Think About It
  • Next Door
  • Next Door 2
  • If You're Happy, Let's Hold Hands
  • Being Next Door
name: Vol. 1

description: Katie & Amy Cassidy are on a mission to find out just who or what is responsible for their parent's death. Is it the government that their parents worked for in a special division as supernatural hunters, or is the answer something even more sinister and dark…?
name: In The Beginning

description: Collecting issues 1-5 of the magical Old-Western saga that introduced Vesper Grey and Corrick to comics.
name: TPB

description:
Out Of The Frying Pan And Into The Fire

Gazzer is forced to run for his life after firing into the wrong girl. While trying to escape his pursuers Gazzer lands into an even bigger mess on the planet of Mars.

If Flash Gordon was a scumbag ned from Glasgow, this would be his story.
name: Out Of The Frying Pan And Into The Fire

description: The life of a successful functionary Timur has turned upside down when he is diagnosed with brain tumor. Illness and fate lead him to a Gypsy camp where an old witch implants the soul of a Gypsy baron's murdered son into his body. Now Timur has only 40 days to find out who killed the young Gypsy to keep his own soul. Meanwhile his new gypsy soul is getting stronger and Timur's bond with reality weakens.

Saint Germaine witnesses the events of one of William Shakespeare’s most tragic characters. Formerly an influential force with the young Prince Hal, Falstaff is ostracized by Hal when he assumes the throne as King Henry the V. While Henry prepares for his epic battle at Agincourt which led to the eventual unification of his kingdoms of France and England, Falstaff must stay behind and tells Saint Germaine of his tale. Saint Germaine is a being who claims immortality yet has died a thousand deaths. He has traversed the paths of mankind for untold years. He is the purveyor of light in a world slowly being consumed by shadows. He is Saint Germaine and death to him is nothing more than a state of consciousness.
name: TPB

volume.name: Saint Germaine: The Tragedy of Falstaff

description: AW YEAH COMICS presents SAMI the Samurai Squirrel! the exciting new spin-off series by Scoot McMahon! When the critters of Woodbriar are under attack, Sami the samurai squirrel is there to protect them! Join Sami and friends as they battle Ninjas, Pirates and a Cyber-Yeti (that's right, CYBER-YETI)!! This action-packed first issue also features artwork and stories from famous cartoonists Art Baltazar, Franco and many more! An AW YEAH COMICS! Original series! Created by cartoonist SCOOT McMAHON! AW YEAH Adventure!

Meet Christian Savage, vampire hunter in the wildest backlands of the Wild West. Abandoned by his parents at birth and raised by a kindly priest, Savage was momentarily lured to the black arts of the occult and it cost him the life of the priest. Now Savage roams the countryside ridding the frontier of the supernatural enemies of civilization, until his mission brings him to the last two people he ever expected to meet. Collects issues 1-5. Includes the bonus tale "Bounties: The Candy Heiress".
name: TPB

description: Sherlock Holmes confronts the split persona of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde! Holmes and Watson seek to uncover the terrible secret that is plaguing their good friend, the esteemed Dr. Jekyll. When word gets out that the doctor is allowing the deranged Mr. Hyde free access to his wealth, Holmes realizes that something, no matter how improbable, is wrong. But is the value of a friendship worth more than life itself? Holmes must make that decision. Collects issues 1-2.
name: TPB

volume.name: Sherlock Holmes: Dr. Jekyll & Mr. Holmes

description: A budding reporter attempts to uncover the disappearance of Holmes in his retirement years, only to find that Holmes has a new passion and it deals with corpses. As a bonus, included within this release is “The AMAZEing Mr. Holmes” short story as Holmes is put to the test to see if he can solve a challenging maze.
name: TPB

description: Josie, who’s from a prominent family, has been living in self-imposed exile in Paris after being labeled as a whore. On a lonely Christmas night, she is startled to find a stranger watching her as she entertains herself at a window. The man introduces himself as Adam. They hit it off so well that they decide to have dinner together, which leads to spending a night. After an intense night, Josie feels content but becomes enraged the moment she discovers Adam’s identity!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Today He's Going Camping

In which Sporkman breaks time and keeps smashing the pieces.
name: Today He's Going Camping

description: Siegel and Shuster created the first of the great comic book superheroes, and their square-jawed defender of justice has been personified by the esteemed actor George Reeves and the heroic in his own right Christopher Reeve. The stories of the men behind the cape give Superman his power.
name: TPB

volume.name: The Supermen Behind the Cape: Christopher Reeve, George Reeves, Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster

description:
The Trials of Francis Bear is Gregory Mackay's second book-length expedition into the world of the itinerant, inebriate and inventive Francis Bear. Distracted by folly, and motivated to fabricate, Francis challenges the world around him - indelibly. He seeks pleasure from the bottle, finds opportunity in mistakes and never really gets anything right.

That is until he goes to war...

"I have to do it to protect the children." Jodi's passion was what got her selected to be principal of a school at her young age. The majority of the children's parents are employed at a factory, which has now been bought over and is under threat of closure. The president of the acquiring company is a skilled and famous businessman, Leo Jefferson, whose ability paves the way in the fiercely competitive world of finance. With a decision firmly set in her heart, she knows the only way to get through to such a man is to negotiate directly with him—on that advice, Jodi decides to sneak into his luxury hotel room.
name: Vol. 1

description: An elderly couple volunteers for a visionary rejuvenation procedure. When the procedure experiences a terminal complication, the couple is faced with severely deformed, intellectually superior clones. Soon, it becomes clear that only one version of each individual can survive, and the war for dominance begins.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The cold winds blow through the Victorian city streets and the hinterlands alike, but our saucy steampunk sweethearts will keep your gears running warm!

Note: The digital edition (7/16/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

It has been called the turning point of the Vietnam War. Although it was a military victory for the United States, the ramifications of the Tet Offensive drove American public opinion back home against the war, led to the highest casualty rates of U.S. soldiers, and re-energized the draft process. The Tet Offensive was the beginning of the end to the Vietnam War. Don Lomax's Vietnam Journal series has been hailed for its realistic and thought provoking approach and its Lomax's skill in telling true tales of the war that brought such divisiveness to the American public.
name: Book Five

description: Collecting the entire first arc of Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's Sherlock Holmes and Dr John Watson re-envisioning as African Americans living in New York City's famous Harlem district. Watson, an Afghanistan war vet, works in an inner-city clinic; Holmes, a local P.I. who takes unusual cases. When one of them ends up in Watson's emergency room, the unlikely duo strike up a partnership to find a missing girl. Watson & Holmes bump heads along the way as they enter a labyrinth of drugs, guns, gangs and a conspiracy that goes higher and deeper than they could have imagined. Containing epilogue issue #5 as well as chock full of extra material on the evolution of a new classic.
name: Vol. 1

description: This will be a violent story depicting a zombie outbreak within a primitive and amoral society. The dialogue provided comes from an unseen narrator. This will not be a family friendly story. It will show the choices and struggles our early ancestors faced with one goal in mind: survival.

The series relaunch previewed in the recent issue 0 continues here. Join creator Dan Mendoza for the all new adventures of the cult hit series featuring his undead anti-hero, Zombie Tramp, now brought to life by the amazing talents of new superstar artist, TMChu.

It's kinky supernatural fun as Zombie Tramp hits the road, starting in... Sin City of course!

Black Widow is an Avenger and an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. But on her own time, she searches for atonement for her past as a KGB assassin - in ways those teams just wouldn't approve of. The Widow goes undercover in Russia - but from its cold streets, the Hand of God reaches out to crush her?and it is as merciless as its name. Outmatched by the brute force of this powerful new villain, Natasha discovers a deadly plot that spans the entire globe. Paris, London, Montenegro - Natasha is in a race against time, with nowhere to turn for answers. Black Widow's strength and cunning will be put to the test as she follows the trail of blood and destruction to the beginning, but can she locate the entity behind the attacks? Collecting BLACK WIDOW (2014) #1-6 and material from ALL-NEW MARVEL NOW! POINT ONE #1.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Black Widow: The Finely Woven Thread

description:
The Guardians of the Galaxy, the Avengers of outer space, blast out of DisneyXD's hit animated series and into your hands! When Michael Korvac escapes his alien abductors, he flees home to Earth and seeks the Avengers' protection. For Earth's Mightiest Heroes, defending Korvac will mean battling the Guardians of the Galaxy - but why? The Korvac confusion continues as Spider-Man gets involved, traveling into deep space with the Guardians to take on Korvac... and the alien Chitauri! Hulk and his agents of S.M.A.S.H. encounter the cosmic Collector on a simulated paradise world?but can they ever escape it? Relive Rocket Raccoon's classic comic-book debut, as the feisty, furry film star matches wits with the Hulk! Collecting MARVEL UNIVERSE AVENGERS: EARTH'S MIGHTIEST HEROES #18, MARVEL UNIVERSE ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #22, MARVEL UNIVERSE HULK: AGENTS OF S.M.A.S.H. #4, and INCREDIBLE HULK (1968) #271.
